¶ Just sit right back
    and you'll hear a tale ¶

00:06.407 --> 00:08.473
¶ A tale of a fateful trip ¶

00:08.542 --> 00:13.078
¶ That started from this tropic
port aboard this tiny ship ¶

00:13.147 --> 00:15.446
¶ The mate was
     a mighty sailin' man ¶

00:15.515 --> 00:17.716
¶ The Skipper brave and sure ¶

00:17.785 --> 00:20.152
¶ Five passengers
      set sail that day ¶

00:20.220 --> 00:22.187
¶ For a three hour tour ¶

00:22.256 --> 00:25.290
¶ A three hour tour ¶

00:25.359 --> 00:27.325
[thunder rumbling]

00:27.394 --> 00:29.528
¶ The weather started
     getting rough ¶

00:29.597 --> 00:31.730
¶ The tiny ship was tossed ¶

00:31.798 --> 00:34.332
¶ If not for the courage
    of the fearless crew ¶

00:34.401 --> 00:36.568
¶ The Minnow would be lost ¶

00:36.637 --> 00:38.670
¶ The Minnow would be lost ¶

00:38.739 --> 00:40.772
¶ The ship set ground
     on the shore ¶

00:40.841 --> 00:43.875
¶ Of this uncharted
      desert isle ¶

00:43.944 --> 00:46.177
¶ With Gilligan ¶

00:46.246 --> 00:48.279
¶ The Skipper too ¶

00:48.348 --> 00:50.582
¶ The millionaire ¶

00:50.651 --> 00:52.951
¶ And his wife ¶

00:53.020 --> 00:55.720
¶ The movie star ¶

00:55.789 --> 00:57.355
¶ And the rest ¶

00:57.424 --> 01:02.728
¶ Are here on Gilligan's Isle ¶

